Below is a simple HTML template for a site centered around the name "Kirsten" with some jokes added.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Kirsten's Jokes</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #F0EDE5;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 48px;
            color: #663399;
        }
        hr {
            width: 50%;
            margin: 30px auto;
        }
        .joke-container {
            max-width: 400px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #5B5B5B;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to Kirsten's Jokes!</h1>
    <hr>
    <div class="joke-container">
        <p><b>Joke 1:</b> Why couldn't the bicycle stand up by itself? Because it was two-tired!</p>
        <p><b>Joke 2:</b> Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!</p>
        <p><b>Joke 3:</b> Did you hear about the mathematician who’s afraid of negative numbers? He'll stop at nothing to avoid them!</p>
        <p><b>Joke 4:</b> Want to hear a construction joke? Oh never mind, I'm still working on that one!</p>
        <p><b>Joke 5:</b> Why don't some couples go to the gym? Because some relationships don't work out!</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

You can copy and paste the code above into a new HTML file, and open it using a web browser to see the site. This design is a simple and minimalist page that displays a header with the name "Kirsten" followed by a few light-hearted jokes.
